class.name: Phaser.Ellipse

parameters.name: x
parameters.help: The X coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.

parameters.name: y
parameters.help: The Y coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.

parameters.name: width
parameters.help: The overall width of this ellipse.

parameters.name: height
parameters.help: The overall height of this ellipse.

class.help: Creates a Ellipse object. A curve on a plane surrounding two focal points.

public.name: clone
public.help: Returns a new Ellipse object with the same values for the x, y, width, and height properties as this Ellipse object.

parameters.name: output
parameters.help: Optional Ellipse object. If given the values will be set into the object, otherwise a brand new Ellipse object will be created and returned.

public.name: contains

returns.help: True if the coordinates are within this ellipse, otherwise false.

public.help: Return true if the given x/y coordinates are within the Ellipse object.

parameters.name: x
parameters.help: The X value of the coordinate to test.

parameters.name: y
parameters.help: The Y value of the coordinate to test.

public.name: copyFrom
public.help: Copies the x, y, width and height properties from any given object to this Ellipse.

public.name: copyTo
public.help: Copies the x, y, width and height properties from this Ellipse to any given object.

public.name: getBounds
public.help: Returns the framing rectangle of the ellipse as a Phaser.Rectangle object.

public.name: setTo
public.help: Sets the members of the Ellipse to the specified values.

parameters.name: x
parameters.help: The X coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.

parameters.name: y
parameters.help: The Y coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.

parameters.name: width
parameters.help: The overall width of this ellipse.

parameters.name: height
parameters.help: The overall height of this ellipse.

public.name: toString

returns.help: A string representation of the instance.

public.help: Returns a string representation of this object.

public.name: bottom
public.help: The sum of the y and height properties. Changing the bottom property of an Ellipse doesn't adjust the y property, but does change the height.
public.inlineHelp: Gets or sets the bottom of the ellipse.

public.name: empty
public.help: Determines whether or not this Ellipse object is empty. Will return a value of true if the Ellipse objects dimensions are less than or equal to 0; otherwise false.\nIf set to true it will reset all of the Ellipse objects properties to 0. An Ellipse object is empty if its width or height is less than or equal to 0.
public.inlineHelp: Gets or sets the empty state of the ellipse.

public.name: height
public.inlineHelp: The overall height of this ellipse.

public.name: right
public.help: The x coordinate of the rightmost point of the Ellipse. Changing the right property of an Ellipse object has no effect on the x property, but does adjust the width.
public.inlineHelp: Gets or sets the value of the rightmost point of the ellipse.

public.name: top
public.help: The top of the Ellipse. The same as its y property.
public.inlineHelp: Gets or sets the top of the ellipse.

public.name: width
public.inlineHelp: The overall width of this ellipse.

public.name: x
public.inlineHelp: The X coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.

public.name: y
public.inlineHelp: The Y coordinate of the upper-left corner of the framing rectangle of this ellipse.
